   279	  // 2. B0 on GPU 0 and B0 on GPU 1 wait for each other (block_barrier #0)
   280	  // 3. B0 on GPU 0 gather and sum the B0 chunks from GPU 1, that are in the GPU 0 responsibility
   281	  //    part (the first half of the message, see GPU responsibility row above)
   282	  // 3bis. Likewise, B0 on GPU 1 copies and sum the chunks for GPU 0,
   283	  //       where GPU 1 is responsible: the second half of the message.
   284	  // 4. B0 on GPU 0 and B0 on GPU 1 wait for each other (block_barrier #1)
   285	  // 5. B0 writes result to local_output. It gathers each chunk from its responsible GPU.
   286	  //    For example, here it reads the first chunk from GPU 0 and second chunk from GPU 1.
   287	  //
   288	  // With COPY_INPUT == false, skip step 1. and use gpu_barrier instead of block barrier during step 2.
